        "text": "I am resolved what to do",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The first part of the parable teaches, then, this great and all-important lesson to men - that they will do well to provide against the day of dismissal from life. The second part points out very vividly how kindness, charity, beneficence, towards those poorer, weaker, more helpless than ourselves is one way, and that a very sure and direct way, cf. so providing against the inevitable dissmission, or death. Luke 16:4",
